snippet: President Petro O. Poroshenko of Ukraine said the withdrawal of Russian forces augmented the chances for a lasting cease-fire in the southeast.
abstract: Ukraine's Pres Petro O Poroshenko says the bulk of Russian forces have withdrawn from Ukrainian territory, move he says heightens chances for lasting cease-fire in southeast.

byline.contributor: Andrew Higgins contributed reporting from Brussels, Alison Smale from Berlin, and David M. Herszenhorn from Moscow.

lead_paragraph: President Petro O. Poroshenko of Ukraine said the withdrawal of Russian forces augmented the chances for a lasting cease-fire in the southeast.

headline.main: Most Russian Forces Now Out of Ukraine, Kiev Says
headline.print_headline: Most Russian Forces Now Out of Ukraine, Kiev Says
